# 🌟 REST Principles

## 1️⃣ Client-Server Architecture

Client and Server work independently.

---

## 2️⃣ Stateless

Each request contains all the required information.

The server does not remember previous requests.

Example:

```text id="rest3"
Request 1 → Login

Request 2 → Send Token

Request 3 → Get Data
```

---

## 3️⃣ Cacheable

Responses can be cached for better performance.

---

## 4️⃣ Uniform Interface

REST APIs follow standard HTTP methods and URL patterns.

---

## 5️⃣ Layered System

The client does not know whether it is connected directly to the server or through intermediaries.

