# ⭐ REST API Best Practices

* Use Proper HTTP Methods
* Use Meaningful URLs
* Return Correct Status Codes
* Keep APIs Stateless
* Use JSON Format
* Handle Exceptions Properly
* Validate User Input
* Version APIs

Example:

```text id="rest35"
/api/v1/students
```

---

# ❌ Common Mistakes

* Using verbs in URLs
* Returning incorrect status codes
* Ignoring validation
* Not handling exceptions
* Exposing sensitive data

